# Routing Contracts

Preserve public route behavior unless the task explicitly changes product requirements:

- `/` and `/download` render the download experience.
- `/:username/:slug` renders public collection.
- `/:username/:slug?invite=<token>` remains invitation-first when token is valid.

# Sticky Navigator Contracts

When editing collection navigation/scroll behavior:

- Preserve `data-item-id` and `data-nav-id` data attribute contracts.
- Keep navbar/sticky offset assumptions consistent (`h-14` / 56px baseline).
- Verify active pill tracking and scroll-centering behavior after changes.

# Regression Awareness

- Treat these contracts as user-facing behavior guarantees.
- If a refactor risks behavior drift, call it out and validate manually.
